  <mads:note type="source">Megalē Hellēnikē enkyklopaideia (Stephanos ho Alexandreus, active 7th century,
    Greek philosopher)</mads:note>
  <mads:note type="source">Stephanus, of Athens. Commentary on Hippocrates' aphorisms, Sections I-II, 
    1985: page 20 (Stephanus of Alexandria the philosopher, author of two commentaries on Aristotle 
    and an astronomical work)</mads:note>
  <mads:note type="source">Le commentaire astronomique aux Tables faciles de Ptolémée attribué
    à Stéphanos d'Alexandrie, 2016: title page (Stéphanos d'Alexandrie) page 3 (le philosophe 
    Stéphanos d'Alexandrie) page 4 (Stephanus the Alexandrian philosopher)</mads:note>
  <mads:note type="source">The Oxford dictionary of Byzantium: volume 3, page 1953 (Stephen of 
    Alexandria, philosopher, probably born in Athens between about 550 and 555,
    died after 619/620, perhaps in Constantinople; the scholar Wanda Wolska-Conus
    believes that he is the same person as Stephanus of Athens; in Alexandria, 
    he was close to the circle of John Philoponos; he wrote a commentary on 
    several treatises of Aristotle and a commentary on Ptolemy; he was probably
    the author of an explanation of the astronomical commentary of Theon)</mads:note>
  <mads:note type="notFound">Oxford classical dictionary</mads:note>
